       </tr>
       
       <tr>
         <td height="22" align="left" valign="top" class="inner_head3"> COMMON WEALTH SCIENTIFIC AND INDUSTRIAL RESEARCH ORGANISATION (CSIRO) </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
             <tr>
               <td width="230" align="left" valign="top"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                   <tr>
                     <td align="left" valign="top"><img src="images/inner/cisro.png" width="201" height="139" style="padding:1px; border:solid 1px #CCCCCC" /></td>
                   </tr>
               </table></td>
               <td align="left" valign="top"><div align="justify">SCCL entered into Relationship arrangement with CSIRO, Australia on 01.02.2006 at New Delhi. This arrangement facilitates R &amp; D projects in Strata Mechanics, ventilation and other related subjects with specific reference to Longwall Mining. Sri R.H.Khwaja, IAS, C &amp; MD, SCCL and Dr. Cliff Mallett, Acting Chief, CSIRO exchanged the relationship arrangement. Mr. Bob Baldwin, Parliamentary Secretary to Australia is also present.</div></td>
             </tr>
         </table></td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td height="25" align="left" valign="top" class="inner_head2"> CONSULTANCY SERVICES OFFERED BY SCCL</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top" class="inner_head3"> With over 125 years of experience in Coal mining, SCCL has acquired expertise in different activities. </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top"> SCCL is proposing to take-up consultancy jobs related to mining in the following areas.</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td height="22" align="left" valign="top" class="inner_head3">1. Coal Exploration and Evaluation </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top"><p align=justify>SCCL is having an ISO 9001 : 2008 accredited Exploration department with highly qualified, academically brilliant , strong inter disciplinary experts comprising of 38 Geologists, 11 Drilling Engineers, 10 Geo-physicists and 5 Hydro- Geologists bringing out the Insights of the the Earth&rsquo;s hidden Treasure. SCCL is equipped with 3 numbers of sophisticated digital Geo-Physical Loggers. The drilling in SCCL is around 1,30,000 metres per annum. So far SCCL prepared 185 Geological Reports and 39 Geo-Models pertaining to Godavari valley coalfield and coal blocks allocated to others.</p></td>
       </tr>
       
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top"><ul>
             <li>Reconnaissance survey and field mapping</li>
           <li>Drilling (coring & non-coring)</li>
           <li>Geological logging, Geophysical logging and Hydrogeological investigations</li>
           <li>Preparation of Geological Reports</li>
		   <li>Digital Geo-model using MINEX software</li>
           <ul>
               <li>Preparation of computerised geological 3-D models</li>
             <li>Preparation of Geological plans - Geological cross sections, Structural / seam folio / iso-parting plans etc.,</li>
			 <li>Assessment of coal quality</li>
			 <li>Estimation of coal reserves</li>
           </ul>
		   <li>Conducting Hydro-geological tests and preparation of reports and hydro-geological modelling by using "modflow" software.</li>
		   <li>Geotechnical mapping, core photography and application of "core profiler" software.</li>
		   <li>Geophysical and Geotechnical studies</li>
         </ul></td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top" style="border-bottom:solid 1px #CCCCCC" >&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td height="25" align="left" valign="top" class="inner_head3">2. Mine Planning, Design and Construction</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top"><p align=justify>SCCL has an ISO 9001:2008 accredited Project Planning department, capable of undertaking Coal mine planning in detail. It has 36 professionals in the fields of Opencast mining, Underground mining, Environmental Engineering, Survey, Mechanical & Electrical Engineering, Financial Evaluation Experts (Econometrician & Finance), Industrial Engineering, Geology and Civil Engineering and other trained personnel.</p></td></tr>
         <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
          <tr><td align="left" valign="top"><p align=justify>The department is using latest versions of mine planning software like MINEX, CARLSON and Auto CAD for preparation of Project Reports. </p></td></tr>
          <tr>
         <td align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
       </tr>
          <tr><td align="left" valign="top"><p align=justify>Project Planning department has so far prepared 125 Project Reports and 91 Mining plans since IXth Plan (1997-98).</p> </p>  </td></tr>
       <tr><td align="left" valign="top">Major works undertaken by the department are:
       <ul>
       <li>Preparation of Techno-Economic Feasibility Reports for Opencast & Underground Mines.</li>
       <li>Preparation of Mining Plans under Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Act 1957. </li>
